			<node ID="ID_910401505" TEXT="The Global Descriptor Table (GDT) is a table in memory that defines the processors memory segments. The GDT sets the behavior of the segment registers and helps to ensure that protected mode operates smoothly. GDTR . The GDT is pointed to by a special register in the x86 chip the GDT Register or simply the GDTR. The GDTR is 48 bits long." />
